        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Talladega National Forest, or 10 miles southeast of Centreville,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lawley, Talladega National Forest, Chilton County Motor Sports Park,
Randolph, Oakmulgee, and Trio.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
